title: Shamsiddin Shanbiyev
text:
Shamsiddin Asroridinovich Shanbiyev (, ; born 18 February 1997) is a Russian <a href="association%20football">football</a> player of <a href="Tajiks">Tajik</a> origin. He plays for <a href="FC%20Irtysh%20Omsk">Irtysh Omsk</a>.
Club career.
He made his debut in the <a href="Russian%20Football%20National%20League">Russian Football National League</a> for <a href="FC%20Spartak-2%20Moscow">FC Spartak-2 Moscow</a> on 7 April 2016 in a game against <a href="FC%20Baltika%20Kaliningrad">FC Baltika Kaliningrad</a>.
On 22 October 2018, he signed with <a href="FC%20Ural%20Yekaterinburg">FC Ural Yekaterinburg</a>. As the transfer window was closed at the time, he was not eligible to play for Ural until 2019. On 19 January 2021, his Ural contract was terminated by mutual consent.
On 15 January 2021, he signed with Belarusian club <a href="FC%20Isloch%20Minsk%20Raion">FC Isloch Minsk Raion</a>.
